    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Rear Bumper Assembly</title>
        <para>The rear bumper assembly is a steel bumper bolted to the chassis frame section with offset mounting
            brackets. The bumper is mounted to the brackets with eight carriage bolts with lock nuts and washers.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate, loosen and remove the mounting screws securing the bumper transition cover on the
                body panels and bumper ends.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47005120" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47005120.webp" filename="../figg47/g47005120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 120. Bumper Transition Cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">REAR BUMPER SIDE MOUNTING BOLTS (2 EACH SIDE)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">REAR BUMPER MOUNTING BOLTS (4)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">BUS REAR BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">BUMPER TRANSITION COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">BUMPER TRANSITION COVER MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the bumper mounting bolts and lock nuts and washers on the bumper assembly. These
                bolts are located on the outboard section of the bumper assembly on each side at the rear of the bus
                body.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47005121" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47005121.webp" filename="../figg47/g47005121.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 121. Rear Bumper Side Support Brackets (Driver Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">REAR BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">REAR BUMPER SIDE MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">REAR BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT BRACKET ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the lock nuts and washers (2 each side) securing the bumper assembly to
                the mounting brackets on the bumper mounting assembly located outboard each side of the body.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47005122" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g47005122" filename="../figg47/g47005122.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 122. Bumper Mounting Bracket and Bolts with Tow Hook Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">SQUEAK PAD</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">BUMPER FRAME MOUNTING BRACKET BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">REAR BUMPER MOUNTING BOLTS, NUTS AND WASHERS</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">REAR BUMPER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">REAR BUMPER LOWER FLANGE SECTION</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">REAR TOW HOOK ASSEMBLY (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">CHASSIS FRAME SECTION</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant steadying the bumper, loosen and remove the remaining 4 mounting bolts at
                the rear of the bumper assembly from the bumper mounting brackets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bumper assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
